PART 4: UNPAID ABSENCE - SYSTEM CHECKS
When Unpaid Absence Logged:
Checks Performed:
✓ Date valid (not future, within cutoff)
✓ Employee active
✓ No duplicate
✓ Can coexist with work same day
✓ Admin categorizes type
✓ Weekly hours recalculated (unpaid = 0h)
✓ No vacation/overtime balance impact
✓ Compliance warnings (patterns)
✓ Payroll deduction applied
✓ Audit trail created
Impact:
💰 Salary deduction ONLY
✅ Vacation balance: NOT reduced
✅ Overtime balance: NOT reduced
✅ Carryover: NOT affected
✅ Weekly hours: Unpaid = 0h (doesn't count)

PART 5: AUTO-FILL MISSING ENTRIES ✅ NEW FEATURE
When: No entry logged within 72 hours
Action:
System auto-creates entry
Start time: 9:00 AM (configurable)
Duration: Daily hours from settings (default 8h)
Type: Work
Flagged: "auto-filled" for visibility
Implementation: Scheduled job (cron)

PART 6: BALANCE MANAGEMENT MODAL
Tab 1: Carryover ✅ UPDATED
Purpose: Set initial carryover from previous year
Use: Only on Day 1 of company setup
Fields:
Vacation carryover (days)
Overtime carryover (hours)
Limit: 100% carryover allowed (no max in system)
Status: Always enabled, no toggle
Tab 2: Payout ✅ UPDATED
Purpose: Record balance paid to employee
Effect: Reduces available balance
Fields:
Vacation days paid out
Overtime hours paid out
Reason (for audit trail)
Example: Employee requests 40h overtime → Record as payout
Tab 3: Manual Adjustment ❌ DELETED
Reason: Too risky, bypass normal calculations
Alternative: Use Payout for corrections

PART 7: DATA STORAGE & AUDIT TRAIL ✅ NEW
New Database Tables Required:
work_percentage_history
employee_id, percentage_value, effective_date, 
previous_percentage, reason, changed_by, changed_at

Why Critical: Vacation calculation changes when % changes mid-year
balance_audit_trail
employee_id, change_type (carryover/payout/adjustment), 
field (vacation/overtime), previous_value, new_value, 
reason, changed_by, changed_at, month, year

Why Critical: Swiss law requires proof of all balance changes
time_entries (updated)
Add fields: 
  - absence_type (set by admin)
  - modified_by (who categorized)
  - modified_at (when)
  - is_auto_filled (flag for auto-created)


PART 8: EMPLOYMENT TYPES
Full-time (Vollzeit)
Work percentage: 100%
Vacation: Full annual entitlement
Timesheet: Required
Part-time (Teilzeit)
Work percentage: 20-99%
Vacation: Pro-rated
Timesheet: Required
Hourly (Stundenlohn)
Vacation: Included in hourly rate
Timesheet: NOT required (no vacation module)
Premium: Included in hourly calc

PART 9: ALL CLIENT DECISIONS (MARCH 6, 2026)
✅ APPROVED FOR PHASE 1
✅ Time entry: Work/Free only (employee), admin categorizes
✅ Vacation: Age-based (20-49=25d, 50+=30d), pro-rated
✅ Overtime: Target vs actual hours
✅ Carryover: 100%, always enabled, no max limit
✅ Payout tracking with audit trail
✅ Premiums: Sunday 50%, Holiday 100%, Extratime 25%
✅ Auto-fill missing entries after 72 hours
✅ PDF export for labor authority
✅ Work percentage history tracking
✅ Audit trail (legal requirement)
❌ DELETED FROM SCOPE
❌ Timer (play/pause/stop) - Manual entry sufficient
❌ Night shift premium (22:00-06:00) - Too complex
❌ Manual adjustment tab - Too risky
❌ Carryover toggle - Always on
❌ Approval workflow - Phase 2 if needed
❌ WhatsApp API - Not suitable

PART 10: COMPLETE DATA CALCULATIONS
Vacation Earned (Pro-Rata Example)
Employee: Anna Schmidt
Age: 28
Work %: 80%
Start: June 1, 2025
Entitlement: 25 days (age 20-49)

Earned in 2025:
= 25 × (214/365) × 0.80
= 25 × 0.586 × 0.80
= 11.7 days

Vacation Balance
Earned: 11.7 days
Carryover: 5.0 days (100%)
Used: -8 days
Payouts: -1.5 days
Adjustment: 0

Balance = 11.7 + 5.0 - 8 - 1.5 = 7.2 days

Overtime Balance
Worked: 1,650h
Target: 1,620h (23 workdays × 8h × 100%)
Difference: +30h
Carryover: +10h
Compensation used: -40h (5 days × 8h)
Payouts: -15h

Balance = 30 + 10 - 40 - 15 = -15h (owes 15h)

Weekly Status
Week 50:
Mon-Fri: 40h
Saturday: 0h
Sunday: 8h work (Sunday premium: +50% = +4h)
Total: 48h + 4h = 52h

Status: 🔴 EXTRATIME (>48h)
Action: Grant 1 compensation day (8h) to bring below 48h


